## 3. User Model

The user model is intentionally simple for V1. One user, one login. No roles, no team access, no multi-user orgs.

**User → many Companies → each has Industry + Ad Accounts**

A user (e.g., an agency owner) logs in and sees a list of all their companies. Each company represents a client or business. Each company has one industry tag and one or more connected ad accounts (Google Ads, Meta Ads). The user selects a company and views that company's benchmarks.

### Key Rules

- Industry is set per company during onboarding (self-selected by user)
- Spend tier is calculated automatically per ad account from trailing 30-day spend
- Benchmarks are platform-specific (Google Ads benchmarks vs. Google Ads peers, Meta vs. Meta)
- No company-to-company data sharing — all benchmarks are aggregated and anonymized

