## 5. Spend Tier Model

Spend tiers are dynamic and percentile-based. Rather than hardcoded dollar ranges, accounts are grouped into quartiles within their industry and platform based on trailing 30-day spend.

### Quartile Definitions

| Tier | Percentile Range | Label in UI |
|------|-----------------|-------------|
| Q1 | 0th – 25th percentile | "Lower spend tier" |
| Q2 | 25th – 50th percentile | "Mid-low spend tier" |
| Q3 | 50th – 75th percentile | "Mid-high spend tier" |
| Q4 | 75th – 100th percentile | "Top spend tier" |

### Minimum Pool Rules

- Quartile benchmarks require 20+ accounts in the same industry × platform segment
- If fewer than 20 accounts exist, fall back to full-industry benchmarks (no spend tier split)
- If fewer than 5 accounts exist in an industry × platform, show no benchmark — display "Not enough data yet for your industry"
- Quartiles are recalculated nightly as part of the benchmark refresh job

### Benchmark Key

Every benchmark row is uniquely identified by the composite key:

```
platform × industry × spend_quartile × metric × date
```

