## 7. Database Schema

All tables live in Supabase (Postgres). UUIDs for all primary keys. Timestamps in UTC.

### `users`

Managed by Supabase Auth. Extended with a profile table.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | From Supabase Auth |
| `email` | text (unique) | Login email |
| `full_name` | text | Display name |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | Auto-set |

### `companies`

Each company is a client/business the user manages. This is the core entity for benchmarking.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `user_id` | uuid (FK → users) | Owner of this company |
| `name` | text | Display name (e.g. "PowerBroker AI") |
| `industry_id` | int (FK → industries) | Self-selected during onboarding |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | Auto-set |

### `industries`

Static lookup table. Seeded on deploy.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | serial (PK) | Auto-increment |
| `name` | text | Display name |
| `slug` | text (unique) | URL-safe identifier |

### `ad_accounts`

Each connected Google Ads or Meta Ads account. Belongs to a company.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `company_id` | uuid (FK → companies) | Parent company |
| `platform` | enum (google_ads, meta) | Ad platform |
| `platform_account_id` | text | External account ID from the platform |
| `account_name` | text | Display name from the platform |
| `access_token` | text (encrypted) | OAuth access token |
| `refresh_token` | text (encrypted) | OAuth refresh token |
| `token_expires_at` | timestamptz | Token expiry for refresh logic |
| `is_active` | boolean | Whether data is still being pulled |
| `connected_at` | timestamptz | When the account was first connected |

### `daily_metrics`

Raw daily performance data pulled from ad platform APIs. One row per ad account per date. This is the source of truth for all benchmarking.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `ad_account_id` | uuid (FK → ad_accounts) | Which account this data belongs to |
| `date` | date | The calendar date for this data |
| `impressions` | bigint | Total impressions |
| `clicks` | bigint | Total clicks |
| `spend` | numeric(12,2) | Total spend in account currency |
| `conversions` | numeric(10,2) | Total conversions |
| `conversion_value` | numeric(12,2) | Total conversion value / revenue |
| `pulled_at` | timestamptz | When this data was fetched from the API |

*Unique constraint on (ad_account_id, date) — upsert on each pull.*

### `account_spend_tiers`

Tracks each ad account's current spend quartile. Recalculated nightly.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `ad_account_id` | uuid (FK → ad_accounts) | The account being tiered |
| `industry_id` | int (FK → industries) | Denormalized for query speed |
| `platform` | enum | Denormalized for query speed |
| `quartile` | smallint (1-4) | Current spend quartile |
| `trailing_30d_spend` | numeric(12,2) | Spend sum used for calculation |
| `calculated_at` | timestamptz | When this tier was last calculated |

### `benchmark_cache`

Precomputed benchmark aggregates. Refreshed nightly after spend tiers are recalculated. This is what the dashboard reads from — no live aggregation queries.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Auto-generated |
| `industry_id` | int (FK → industries) | Industry segment |
| `platform` | enum | google_ads or meta |
| `spend_quartile` | smallint (nullable) | 1-4, or NULL for full-industry benchmark |
| `date` | date | Calendar date |
| `metric_name` | text | e.g. cpc, cpm, ctr, roas, cpa |
| `avg_value` | numeric(12,4) | Mean across accounts in segment |
| `median_value` | numeric(12,4) | Median (P50) |
| `p25_value` | numeric(12,4) | 25th percentile |
| `p75_value` | numeric(12,4) | 75th percentile |
| `account_count` | int | Number of accounts in this segment |
| `calculated_at` | timestamptz | When this benchmark was computed |

*Unique constraint on (industry_id, platform, spend_quartile, date, metric_name).*

