## 10. User Flows

### Onboarding (New User)

1. User signs up (email magic link or Google OAuth)
2. Prompted to create their first company — enters name, selects industry from dropdown
3. Prompted to connect at least one ad account (Google Ads or Meta)
4. OAuth flow completes, account appears in their dashboard
5. First data pull is triggered immediately (not waiting for nightly job)
6. User sees their data within minutes; benchmark line appears once enough peer data exists

### Adding a New Company

1. From the company switcher, user clicks "Add Company"
2. Enters company name, selects industry
3. Connects ad accounts for that company
4. Company appears in their company list

### Daily Use

- User logs in → sees company list → selects a company
- Dashboard shows line charts for each metric: their line vs. benchmark line
- User can toggle between metrics (CPC, CPM, CTR, ROAS, CPA)
- User can change date range (last 7d, 30d, 90d, custom)
- User can switch between ad accounts within the company if multiple are connected

