## 12. Security Considerations

- OAuth tokens (access + refresh) must be encrypted at rest in the database — use Supabase Vault or application-level encryption
- All API routes require authentication (Supabase session check)
- Users can only access their own companies and ad accounts (row-level security in Supabase)
- Benchmark data is always aggregated — never expose individual account data to other users
- Minimum account thresholds (5 for industry, 20 for quartile) prevent reverse-engineering individual performance
- Rate limit API routes to prevent abuse

